@startuml 01_login_workflow_dev
title BookRover — Login Workflow (DEV)\nAll Roles: Admin · Group Leader · Seller (new & returning)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam defaultFontSize 13

actor       "User\n(Browser)"         as User
participant "React App\n(localhost:5173)" as FE
participant "FastAPI\n(localhost:8000)" as BE
database    "DynamoDB\n(AWS / local)"  as DB

note over FE, BE
  **DEV environment variables required**
  FE: VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
  BE: APP_ENV=dev
      ADMIN_EMAILS=admin@example.com
      BOOKROVER_TABLE_PREFIX=bookrover
      AWS_REGION, AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
      (or use a local DynamoDB endpoint via AWS_ENDPOINT_URL)
end note

== Step 1 — User submits email on /login ==

User  -> FE : Enter email + click Continue
FE    -> BE : POST /dev/mock-token\n{ "email": "user@example.com" }

note right of BE
  Endpoint only available when
  APP_ENV=dev — returns 404 in prod.
  Token = base64url(email) — NO crypto.
end note

BE   --> FE : 200 { "token": "<base64url>", "email": "user@example.com" }
FE    -> FE : localStorage.setItem('bookrover_token', token)

== Step 2 — Resolve identity via GET /me ==

FE    -> BE : GET /me\nAuthorization: Bearer <base64url>
BE    -> BE : _decode_dev_token() → extract email

alt email in ADMIN_EMAILS config
    BE   --> FE : 200 { roles: ["admin"],\n  seller_id: null, group_leader_id: null }
    FE    -> FE : AuthContext.setMe()\nnavigate("/admin")

else email found in group-leaders table
    BE    -> DB : Scan group-leaders by email
    DB   --> BE : GroupLeader record\n{ group_leader_id, bookstore_ids, ... }
    BE   --> FE : 200 { roles: ["group_leader"],\n  group_leader_id: "uuid",\n  seller_id: null }
    FE    -> FE : AuthContext.setMe()\nnavigate("/dashboard")

else email found in sellers table
    BE    -> DB : Scan sellers by email
    DB   --> BE : Seller record\n{ seller_id, status, ... }
    BE   --> FE : 200 { roles: ["seller"],\n  seller_id: "uuid",\n  group_leader_id: null }
    FE    -> FE : AuthContext.setMe()\nnavigate("/inventory")

else email not found anywhere (new user)
    BE    -> DB : Scan group-leaders — no match
    BE    -> DB : Scan sellers — no match
    BE   --> FE : 200 { roles: [],\n  seller_id: null, group_leader_id: null }
    FE    -> FE : AuthContext.setMe()\nnavigate("/register")
end

== Step 3 — Logout (any role) ==

User  -> FE : Click Logout
FE    -> FE : localStorage.removeItem('bookrover_token')\nAuthContext.setMe(null)\nnavigate("/login")

@enduml
